title: Kazakhstan Producer Prices Change
description: Producer Prices in Kazakhstan increased 17 percent in October of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Producer Prices Change in Kazakhstan averaged 13.31 percent from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 71.70 percent in July of 2008 and a record low of -33.60 percent in July of 2009. Producer prices change refers to year over year change in price of goods and services sold by manufacturers and producers in the wholesale market during a given period. This page provides - Kazakhstan Producer Prices Change- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bureau of National Statistics of the Republic of Kazakhstan
